\p 
\v 1 \w The|strong="H5922"\w* prophets \w Haggai|strong="H2292"\w* \w and|strong="H2148"\w* \w Zechariah|strong="H2148"\w*, \w son|strong="H1247"\w* \w of|strong="H1247"\w* \w Iddo|strong="H5714"\w*, gave messages\f + \fr 5:1 \ft “Gave messages”: literally, “prophesied.” From the reaction of Zerubbabel the messages were to restart the building of the Temple.\f* \w to|strong="H5922"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* \w Jews|strong="H3062"\w* \w in|strong="H5922"\w* \w Judah|strong="H3061"\w* \w and|strong="H2148"\w* \w Jerusalem|strong="H3390"\w* \w from|strong="H1768"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* God \w of|strong="H1247"\w* \w Israel|strong="H3479"\w*, their ruler.
